                <h1 class="heading">"Royal Enfield Launches 'Flying Flea C6' as its Dedicated Electric Vehicle Brand"</h1>
                <h3 class="subheading">Brand Introduction</h3>
                <p><a class="for-link" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="TWBrandDetails" asp-route-brandId="1">Royal Enfield's</a> new sub-brand, "Flying Flea C6," named after one of its historic World War II models, is dedicated to developing and producing electric motorcycles. This brand aims to attract a new generation of riders looking for eco-friendly and efficient urban commuting options, while staying true to Royal Enfield's vintage styling.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Expected Price Range</h3>
                <p>Although Royal Enfield has not yet released official prices for Flying Flea models, industry experts speculate that initial models may start around INR 2.5-3 lakh (USD 3,000-3,600) to remain competitive in the mid-range EV market.</p>
                <div class="row  m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 text-center"><img src="~/images/latestnews/2024/nov/royalenfieldunveilsflyingfleac6evbandforelectricbikes/2.webp" /></div>
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 text-center"><img src="~/images/latestnews/2024/nov/royalenfieldunveilsflyingfleac6evbandforelectricbikes/3.webp" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Design Philosophy</h3>
                <p>Flying Flea models are expected to carry forward Royal Enfield's signature retro look, blended with streamlined, minimalistic designs unique to electric motorcycles. Early concept images suggest a neo-retro aesthetic that combines classic styling with futuristic elements.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Expected Battery and Range</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Battery Type:</span> Lithium-ion, swappable options may be available.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Range:</span> Estimated range of around 100-150 km per charge, suitable for urban and short-distance rides.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Charging Time:</span> Fast-charging capabilities are expected, with approximately 2 hours to reach 80% charge.
                    </li>
                </ol>
                <h3 class="subheading">Performance and Powertrain</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Motor Power:</span> Likely to feature a hub motor producing around 15-20 bhp.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Torque:</span> Instant torque delivery, ideal for city commuting.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Top Speed:</span> Expected top speed of around 90-100 km/h for city-focused models.
                    </li>
                </ol>
                <div class="row  m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 text-center"><img src="~/images/latestnews/2024/nov/royalenfieldunveilsflyingfleac6evbandforelectricbikes/4.webp" /></div>
                    <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 text-center"><img src="~/images/latestnews/2024/nov/royalenfieldunveilsflyingfleac6evbandforelectricbikes/5.webp" /></div>
                </div>
                <h3 class="subheading">Features and Tech</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Connectivity:</span> Flying Flea bikes may come with a smartphone-compatible digital console offering navigation, ride statistics, and remote diagnostics.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Rider Modes:</span> Multiple riding modes for efficiency and performance.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Safety Features:</span> Anti-lock Braking System (ABS), traction control, and regenerative braking for added safety and control.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Suspension and Wheels:</span> Telescopic front forks and dual rear shock absorbers, with lightweight alloy wheels for better agility in urban settings.
                    </li>
                </ol>
                <h3 class="subheading">Eco-Friendly and Urban-Focused</h3>
                <p>Flying Flea is designed primarily for urban environments, offering a clean and quiet alternative for city riders while reducing emissions and operational costs. The brand’s emphasis on swappable battery tech aligns with the growing EV infrastructure.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Market Competition</h3>
                <p>Flying Flea will enter a competitive market with brands like Revolt, Ather, and Bajaj’s EV offerings, which are currently dominating the urban EV motorcycle segment.</p>
            </div>
